{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Touch.screenX","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch_events\">Touch events</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch\"><code>Touch</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/Touch\"><code>Touch()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/clientX\"><code>clientX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/clientY\"><code>clientY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/force\"><code>force</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/identifier\"><code>identifier</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/pageX\"><code>pageX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/pageY\"><code>pageY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusX\"><code>radiusX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusY\"><code>radiusY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/rotationAngle\"><code>rotationAngle</code></a></li><li><em><code>screenX</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenY\"><code>screenY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/target\"><code>target</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Touch Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TouchEvent\"><code>TouchEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TouchList\"><code>TouchList</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"summary","title":"Summary","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Returns the X coordinate of the touch point relative to the screen, not including any scroll offset.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A number.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This example illustrates how to access the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch\"><code>Touch</code></a> object's <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>Touch.screenX</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenY\"><code>Touch.screenY</code></a> properties. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>Touch.screenX</code></a> property is the horizontal (x) coordinate of a touch point relative to the screen in CSS pixels. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenY\"><code>Touch.screenY</code></a> property is the vertical coordinate of a touch point relative to the screen in CSS pixels.</p>\n<p>In following simple code snippet, we assume the user initiates multiple touch contacts on an element with an id of <code>source</code> and then releases contacts with the surface. When the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/touchstart_event\" title=\"touchstart\"><code>touchstart</code></a> event handler is invoked, each touch point's <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>Touch.screenX</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenY\"><code>Touch.screenY</code></a> coordinates are accessed.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Register a touchstart listeners for the 'source' element</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> src <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"source\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nsrc<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'touchstart'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">e</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// Iterate through the touch points and log each screenX/Y coordinate.</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// The unit of each coordinate is CSS pixels.</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> e<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>touches<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">touchpoint[</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>i<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">].screenX = </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>e<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>touches<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>screenX<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">touchpoint[</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>i<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">].screenY = </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>e<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>touches<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>screenY<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/touch-events/#dom-touch-screenx","title":"Touch Events"}],"query":"api.Touch.screenX"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Touch.screenX","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Summary","id":"summary"},{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"Returns the X coordinate of the touch point relative to the screen, not including any scroll offset.","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:19:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Touch.screenX","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/touch/screenx","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/touch/screenx/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f7dae62645a2c735ed6f6ed63f664bf279fdfc4b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch","title":"Touch"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX","title":"Touch.screenX"}],"pageTitle":"Touch.screenX - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}